article.headline: Iona 77, Rhode Island 62
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Steve Burtt scored 19 points and Ricky Soliver added 17 to lead Iona past Rhode Island 77-62 Monday night. Marvin McCullough had seven points and seven assists for the Gaels (4-6), who have won two in a row following a five-game losing streak. Scott Hazleton had 20 points to lead the visiting Rams (2-7). Tyrese Sullivan and Jamaal Wise scored 12 points each for Rhode Island. The lead changed hands seven times in the first half before Iona pulled away to take a 38-29 lead at halftime. Hazleton's basket with 10:59 left pulled Rhode Island within a point at 52-51 but the Rams were not able to tie the game. Iona responded with a 12-3 run and McCullough's basket with 6:53 remaining gave the Gaels a 64-54 lead. Rhode Island made just 11 of 26 free throws in the game, while Iona was 11-of-13 at the line.
